<br>
TOTAL: 59 Cards   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Well, First off, I know that there are too many cards. You need them all. <br>
<br><br>
   Use Yerth first to let loose the Hyren power. Make him start with Monarch Hyren to call more Hyrens. Don&#39;t be afraid to discard a little with Tomorrow&#39;s Jewl, (If you get it in time) because ou really need to get a Gia&#39;s Tome in. Anyway, Use Jungle Hyren Early to piss your opponents off and alter starting energies. Remember to closely read the card text. Play Rayje&#39;s sword if they play annoying creatures like Pyloflufs. When you play a rock or Grass Hyren, don&#39;t be afraid to use Relic Stalkers on yourself.<br>
<br><br>
   If yerth somehow gets defeated, Tony Jones should finish your opponent off. Once again, start with Monarch Hyren and get more of the almighty creatures. Use all the different relics you can. Use Relic mirrors to keep them out.<br>
<br><br>
   If, for whatever reason, you get reduced to Yaki, do not fear! With Staff of Keepers you can play all the Hyrens you want. Take full advantage of Double strike and Timber Hyren&#39;s Tribute.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
***Note***<br>
<br><br>
Hyren&#39;s call says the Hyren you "call" cannot attack, but they can use powers and effects. (Cave and Leaf Hyrens, WINK, WINK) Don&#39;t forget, Have fun.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
